{"cursor":"25076","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox officeholder |name = John Njoroge Michuki |image = |image_size = 200px\n|office = |president = Mwai Kibaki |term_start = 9 January 2008 |term_end = 21\nFebruary 2012 |predecessor = |successor = |birth_date = |birth_place = Muguru\nVillage, Murang'a |death_date = |spouse = |party = Party of National Unity\n|birthname = |nationality = Kenyan |spouse = Josephine Watiri Michuki,\n|relations = |children = |residence = |alma_mater = Worcester College\n|occupation = Politician |profession = |net worth = |cabinet = Minister of\nEnvironment |committees = |portfolio = |religion = Christian |height =\n|signature = |website = }} 'John Njoroge Michuki' (December 1932 â 21 February\n2012) was a Kenyan politician and businessman. He was born at Muguru village,\nIyego Location, Kangema Division in Murangâa District. He was educated in Kenya\nand abroad. Michuki emerged as one of the prominent and long-serving civil\nservants and politicians as well as a businessman in Kenya. Michuki served Kenya\nin various capacities, including Permanent Secretary in the Finance Ministry,\nChairman of the Kenya Commercial Bank, Member of Parliament and Cabinet\nMinister. \"Ministerâs Profile â Hon. John\nMichuki, EGH, MP\" Office of Public Communication,\nhttp://www.communication.go.ke/ministry.asp?personid=1 He was serving his\n4th five-year term as a Member of Parliament for Kangema Constituency. Michuki\nhad a reputation as a \"ruthless\" and efficient manager, and was widely\nacknowledged as among the best performing ministers in President Kibaki's\nGovernment. He was serving as the [http://www.environment.go.ke/ Minister for\nEnvironment and National Resources] at the time of his death.\n","linknr":338,"url":"John_Michuki","recorded":1375074795,"links":["/w/index.php?title=John_Michuki&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=John_Michuki&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_de